### Configure R2 Storage in Payload

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/upload/storage-adapters.mdx

Example configuration for integrating Cloudflare R2 storage into a Payload CMS project, specifying collections and the R2 bucket binding. The `bucket` option should be passed in the environment where Payload is running (e.g., Cloudflare Worker).

```ts
export default buildConfig({
  collections: [Media],
  storage: [
    r2Storage({
      collections: {
        media: true,
      },
      bucket: cloudflare.env.R2,
    }),
  ],
})
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Cloudflare D1 SQLite Adapter

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/sqlite.mdx

Initialize the D1 adapter by providing the required `binding` property, which should correspond to your D1 database binding in the Cloudflare Worker environment.

```ts
import { sqliteD1Adapter } from '@payloadcms/db-d1-sqlite'

export default buildConfig({
  // Your config goes here
  collections: [
    // Collections go here
  ],
  // Configure the D1 adapter here
  db: sqliteD1Adapter({
    // D1-specific arguments go here.
    // `binding` is required and should match the D1 database binding name in your Cloudflare Worker environment.
    binding: cloudflare.env.D1,
  }),
})
```

### One-click deployment options > Deploy on Cloudflare

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/packages/payload/README.md

Deploying Payload on Cloudflare is a fully self-contained one-click process, utilizing Cloudflare Workers, R2 for uploads, and D1 for a globally replicated database.

--------------------------------

### D1 Database

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/sqlite.mdx

Payload CMS offers a separate adapter for Cloudflare D1, a serverless SQLite database, which is currently in beta. To use it, install "@payloadcms/db-d1-sqlite" and configure it with a "binding" property that matches your D1 database binding name in the Cloudflare Worker environment. This adapter inherits options from the standard SQLite adapter, but replaces connection options with the "binding".

--------------------------------

### Rich Text Field

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/rich-text.mdx

The Rich Text Field enables editors to write and format dynamic content within a user-friendly interface. The content is stored as JSON in the database and can be readily converted into HTML or any other required format for display.

